Class Pipe

  • java.lang.Object
    • dangerzone.blocks.Block
      • blocks.Pipe
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CornerPipe, FiveWayPipe, StraightPipe

    public class Pipe
extends dangerzone.blocks.Block
    Pipes are devices that will draw items from components and deliver them to components that use them. All pipes have at least one input face and one output face. They are solid, and cannot be broken without a pickaxe. If a component calls for an item, any pipes outputting to it will call nearby chests and item suppliers and try to draw an item or block from them, then send that item to its output.

    Currently, all pipes will carry items and blocks a maximum of 8 blocks away. If this limit is exceeded, then the item or block will be left where it was, and will not be sent to the component drawing it.

    Author:
    eaglgenes101
    See Also:
    CornerPipe, FiveWayPipe, StraightPipe
